[
  {
    "id": 30201,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "O tempora, o mores! The Senate knows these things, the consul sees them, and yet this man lives.",
    "source": "First Catilinarian Oration",
    "speech": "In Catilinam I",
    "year": -63,
    "context": "Opening denunciation of Catiline's conspiracy in the Roman Senate."
  },
  {
    "id": 30202,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "How long, Catiline, will you abuse our patience? How long will that madness of yours mock us?",
    "source": "First Catilinarian Oration",
    "speech": "In Catilinam I",
    "year": -63,
    "context": "The famous opening line demanding Catiline leave Rome."
  },
  {
    "id": 30203,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The life of the dead is placed in the memory of the living. Not to know what happened before you were born is to remain a child forever.",
    "source": "Orator",
    "speech": "Orator ad M. Brutum",
    "year": -46,
    "context": "On the value of history and the immortality of great deeds through words."
  },
  {
    "id": 30204,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "We are not born for ourselves alone, but for our country, our friends, and our fellow citizens.",
    "source": "On Duties (De Officiis)",
    "speech": "De Officiis (written as moral treatise)",
    "year": -44,
    "context": "Core Stoic-Roman principle of civic duty."
  },
  {
    "id": 30205,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "A nation can survive its fools, and even the ambitious. But it cannot survive treason from within.",
    "source": "Attributed to Cicero (various orations against internal threats)",
    "speech": "Catilinarian Orations",
    "year": -63,
    "context": "Warning about the danger of domestic enemies."
  },
  {
    "id": 30206,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The welfare of the people is the supreme law.",
    "source": "On the Laws (De Legibus)",
    "speech": "De Legibus",
    "year": -52,
    "context": "Fundamental principle of Roman republican thought."
  },
  {
    "id": 30207,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "In a republic, the voice of the people, when it is the voice of reason and justice, must prevail.",
    "source": "Against Verres",
    "speech": "In Verrem",
    "year": -70,
    "context": "Prosecuting a corrupt governor; defending rule of law."
  },
  {
    "id": 30208,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "Let the welfare of the people be the highest law.",
    "source": "On the Laws (De Legibus)",
    "speech": "De Legibus",
    "year": -52,
    "context": "Salus populi suprema lex esto — a cornerstone of Western legal thought."
  },
  {
    "id": 30209,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "There is no place in a free state for the man who would be master over his fellow citizens.",
    "source": "Philippic 2 (against Mark Antony)",
    "speech": "Philippica II",
    "year": -44,
    "context": "Warning against the rise of another dictator after Caesar."
  },
  {
    "id": 30210,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The only excuse for war is to avoid living under injustice.",
    "source": "On Duties (De Officiis)",
    "speech": "De Officiis",
    "year": -44,
    "context": "Just war theory roots in Roman philosophy."
  },
  {
    "id": 30211,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "A room without books is like a body without a soul.",
    "source": "Personal letters and oratorical reflections",
    "speech": "Various",
    "year": null,
    "context": "Celebrating the civilizing power of literature and learning."
  },
  {
    "id": 30212,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The enemy is within the gates; it is with our own luxury, our own folly, our own criminality that we have to contend.",
    "source": "First Catilinarian Oration",
    "speech": "In Catilinam I",
    "year": -63,
    "context": "Identifying moral decay as the real threat alongside the conspirator."
  },
  {
    "id": 30213,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "To be ignorant of what occurred before you were born is to remain always a child.",
    "source": "Orator",
    "speech": "Orator ad M. Brutum",
    "year": -46,
    "context": "Repeated emphasis on historical knowledge as maturity."
  },
  {
    "id": 30214,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "Liberty is not the power of doing what we like, but the right of being able to do what we ought.",
    "source": "On Duties (De Officiis)",
    "speech": "De Officiis",
    "year": -44,
    "context": "Distinguishing license from ordered freedom."
  },
  {
    "id": 30215,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The safety of the people shall be the highest law.",
    "source": "On the Laws (De Legibus)",
    "speech": "De Legibus",
    "year": -52,
    "context": "Reiteration of the central maxim of the state."
  },
  {
    "id": 30216,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "It is the character of a brave and resolute man not to be ruffled by adversity and not to be elated by prosperity.",
    "source": "On Duties (De Officiis)",
    "speech": "De Officiis",
    "year": -44,
    "context": "Stoic ideal of constancy in public life."
  },
  {
    "id": 30217,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "We must stand against the tyrant not only with arms but with the force of law and the power of words.",
    "source": "Philippic 2 (against Mark Antony)",
    "speech": "Philippica II",
    "year": -44,
    "context": "Defending the Republic through oratory after Caesar's assassination."
  },
  {
    "id": 30218,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "Nothing is more noble, nothing more venerable than fidelity.",
    "source": "On Duties (De Officiis)",
    "speech": "De Officiis",
    "year": -44,
    "context": "On the foundational virtue of trust in society and politics."
  },
  {
    "id": 30219,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The man who is not moved by the suffering of others has no claim to the name of citizen.",
    "source": "Against Verres",
    "speech": "In Verrem",
    "year": -70,
    "context": "Appealing to Roman sense of justice during prosecution of a corrupt official."
  },
  {
    "id": 30220,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "While the sick man still has strength, the physician is called; when the disease has become hopeless, he is dismissed.",
    "source": "First Catilinarian Oration",
    "speech": "In Catilinam I",
    "year": -63,
    "context": "Metaphor for the state acting decisively against internal corruption before it is too late."
  },
  {
    "id": 30221,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The safety of the Republic is the supreme law.",
    "source": "On the Laws",
    "speech": "De Legibus",
    "year": -52,
    "context": "Core principle of Roman law."
  },
  {
    "id": 30222,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "An orator is a good man speaking well.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "Definition of the ideal orator."
  },
  {
    "id": 30223,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The first duty of a man is to be a good citizen.",
    "source": "De Officiis",
    "speech": "De Officiis",
    "year": -44,
    "context": "Civic duty."
  },
  {
    "id": 30224,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "Justice is the foundation of all society.",
    "source": "De Officiis",
    "speech": "De Officiis",
    "year": -44,
    "context": "On justice."
  },
  {
    "id": 30225,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The man who is honest is the happiest.",
    "source": "De Officiis",
    "speech": "De Officiis",
    "year": -44,
    "context": "On honesty."
  },
  {
    "id": 30226,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "We must not only be good, but appear to be good.",
    "source": "De Officiis",
    "speech": "De Officiis",
    "year": -44,
    "context": "On reputation."
  },
  {
    "id": 30227,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The orator must be a master of his subject.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On preparation."
  },
  {
    "id": 30228,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "Eloquence is the art of persuasion.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "Definition."
  },
  {
    "id": 30229,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The greatest orator is he who can move the passions of his hearers.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On emotional appeal."
  },
  {
    "id": 30230,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "A good orator must have a good memory.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On skills."
  },
  {
    "id": 30231,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The orator must be able to think on his feet.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On improvisation."
  },
  {
    "id": 30232,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The voice is the instrument of the orator.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On delivery."
  },
  {
    "id": 30233,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "Gesture is as important as words in oratory.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On delivery."
  },
  {
    "id": 30234,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The orator must know the law.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On knowledge."
  },
  {
    "id": 30235,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "Philosophy is the mother of eloquence.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On background."
  },
  {
    "id": 30236,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The orator must be a student of human nature.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On psychology."
  },
  {
    "id": 30237,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "Wit is a powerful weapon in the orator's arsenal.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On humor."
  },
  {
    "id": 30238,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The orator must adapt his style to his audience.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On adaptation."
  },
  {
    "id": 30239,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "Simplicity is the highest form of eloquence.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On style."
  },
  {
    "id": 30240,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The orator must be sincere.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On ethos."
  },
  {
    "id": 30241,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The orator's character is his greatest asset.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On ethos."
  },
  {
    "id": 30242,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The orator must be able to argue both sides.",
    "source": "De Oratore",
    "speech": "De Oratore",
    "year": -55,
    "context": "On versatility."
  },
  {
    "id": 30243,
    "oratorId": 2,
    "text": "The orator must be a master of language.",
